--- !u!114 &1624779043
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1624779042}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a190e2a2d80544043aa4db4e52a0cf90, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  textcomponent: {fileID: 812778039}
  lines:
  - Shimla. Winter of 1926. The snow does not simply fall here. It settles like silence
    over secrets the mountains have guarded for generations. Tonight the storm is
    relentless."
  - "High above the valley stands the Viceregal Library \u2014 a vast colonial archive
    carved into the mountainside. Within its stone walls rest thousands of books,
    ledgers, and manuscripts gathered from every corner of the empire. Trade routes.
    Botanical records. War journals. Personal letters. History preserved line by
    line. The library was built to protect knowledge."
  - "Inside the building remain only four people. Elias Thorne \u2014 Chief Librarian,
    master of the archive, a rigid man who believed discipline and order were the
    foundation of civilization. Mrs. Eleanor Graves \u2014 administrative steward
    for twenty years. Dr. Arthur Bell \u2014 a visiting botanist. Arjun Singh \u2014
    the young archivist. Tonight the storm sealed them all inside together."
  - Earlier this evening, Elias Thorne discovered three dangerous secrets hidden
    within the records of the library. Secrets that threatened reputations. Secrets
    that threatened careers. Secrets that threatened lives.
  - At 8:42 PM, Elias Thorne lifted a glass of brandy to his lips. Moments later
    he collapsed in his chair. Poison stopped his heart before he could call for
    help. The storm sealed the library. The killer never left."
  textspeed: 0.01
